Privacy Policy
Introduction
At EX Wallet, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your personal information is handled responsibly. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have regarding your data. The EX Wallet app is provided as a free service, and by using it, you consent to the collection and use of information as described in this policy. We will not use or share your information with anyone except as outlined in this Privacy Policy. The terms used herein have the same meanings as in our Terms and Conditions, which are accessible on our website.

Information Collection and Use
To enhance your experience with our Service, we may ask you to provide certain personally identifiable information, such as your name, email address, gender, location, and profile pictures. This information is retained and utilized in accordance with this Privacy Policy to improve our services. Additionally, our app may integrate third-party services that could collect information to help identify you.

Cookies
Cookies are small files that serve as anonymous unique identifiers, sent to your browser from the websites you visit and stored on your device's internal memory. While our Service does not explicitly use cookies, it may incorporate third-party code and libraries that do. You have the option to accept or decline these cookies and to be informed when a cookie is being sent to your device. Please note that if you choose to refuse cookies, you may not be able to access certain features of our Service.

Location Information
Certain services may utilize location data transmitted from your mobile device. We use this information solely for the purposes necessary to provide the designated services.

Device Information
We may collect information from your device in certain circumstances. This data is used to enhance our service offerings and to prevent fraudulent activities. Importantly, this information will not include details that can identify individual users.

Service Providers
We may engage third-party companies and individuals for various purposes, including:

Facilitating our Service;
Providing the Service on our behalf;
Performing Service-related tasks; or
Assisting us in analyzing how our Service is used.
It is important to note that these third parties may have access to your Personal Information solely to perform tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.

Security
We value your trust in providing us your Personal Information and strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect it. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Our Service is not intended for anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take immediate steps to delete that information from our servers. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy periodically. Therefore, we encourage you to review this page regularly for any changes. We will notify you of any modifications by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page, and these changes will take effect immediately upon posting.

Contact Us
If you have any questions or suggestions regarding our Privacy Policy, please do not hesitate to contact us.
